title: Youth unemployment rate in Botswana in 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Youth unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Youth unemployment rate has stayed the same over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2000 and 2001.
The highest Youth unemployment rate, of value 46.62 was reached at Year 2003
Minimum Youth unemployment rate about 30.77 was reached at Year 2008
min_summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, containing a total of 21 data points.
In general Youth unemployment rate has stayed the same over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is roughly decreasing from 1999 to 2000, gradually increasing from 2000 to 2003, slightly decreasing from 2003 to 2006, roughly constant from 2006 to 2008, slightly increasing from 2008 to 2010, and finally roughly constant from 2010 to 2019.
